      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="rubrics-overview" data-step-uuid="460c7e3b-4260-4ba3-9b68-07633fe2ec42">
    <h2 id="rubrics-overview" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Rubrics Overview</h2>
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_cf0729ff-9fe4-4021-be0d-def0160224a2" class="text-block-content">
    <p>A rubric is an assessment tool for communicating expectations and measuring student mastery of a course assignment or assessment. Rubrics are typically comprised of rows and columns. Assessed criteria are defined in rows. Columns are used to define levels of performance for each criterion.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/t5/Admin-Guide/How-do-I-manage-rubrics-in-an-account/ta-p/108" target="_blank">How do I manage rubrics in an account?</a></li>
